  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 200°C (392°F).",
    "Season duck breast with salt and lemon zest.",
    "In a shallow dish, mix mustard, cayenne pepper, pomegranate molasses, and coconut oil. Coat the duck breasts in this mixture.",
    "Place coated duck breasts on a rack in a roasting pan and place under oven preheat. Roast for 30 minutes.",
    "Reduce heat to 150°C (302°F) and continue poaching for an additional 30-40 minutes or until internal temperature reaches 75°C (167°F).",
    "Sprinkle toasted sesame seeds over the top of duck breasts before serving."
